HEADWORD: Clumber
<hw>Clum"ber</hw> <pr>(kl⟦ucr⟧m"b⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Named from the estate of the Duke of Newcastle.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A kind of field spaniel, with short legs and
stout body, which, unlike other spaniels, hunts silently.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

